<bug>
    <id>541442</id>
    <title>Private Browsing unavailable after 3.6 upgrade</title>
    <description>
        <paragraph id="1">
            <sentence id="1.1">User-Agent:       Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 5.1; en-US; rv:1.9.2) Gecko/20100115 Firefox/3.6 (.</sentence>
            <sentence id="1.2">NET CLR 3.5.30729)
Build Identifier: Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 5.1; en-US; rv:1.9.2) Gecko/20100115 Firefox/3.6 (.</sentence>
            <sentence id="1.3">NET CLR 3.5.30729)</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="2">
            <sentence id="2.1">Used private browsing yesterday in 3.5.</sentence>
            <sentence id="2.2">something - used update feature under help menu and successfully upgraded to 3.6.</sentence>
            <sentence id="2.3">Now private browsing is unavailable/greyed out under the Tools menu and the keyboard commands don't work.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="3">
            <sentence id="3.1">I went to about:config, searched on private and found that this entry:  wser.privatebrowsing.autostart    had been changed to "true".</sentence>
            <sentence id="3.2">On a lark, I changed it to 'false' - restarted firefox, and now private browsing is working fine.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="4">
            <sentence id="4.1">Reproducible: Didn't try</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="5">
            <sentence id="5.1">Steps to Reproduce:</sentence>
            <sentence id="5.2">1 Upgrade firefox using menu item under Help</sentence>
            <sentence id="5.3">2 Restart browser</sentence>
            <sentence id="5.4">3 Try private browsing</sentence>
            <sentence id="5.5">Actual Results:</sentence>
            <sentence id="5.6">Private browsing was unavailable as described</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="6">
            <sentence id="6.1">Expected Results:  
Kept the feature available as it was before the upgrade</sentence>
        </paragraph>
    </description>
</bug>
